2301
2302 struct LetBound {
2303 string var, min_name, max_name;
2304 LetBound(const string &v, const string &min, const string &max)
2305 : var(v), min_name(min), max_name(max) {
2306 }
2307 };
2308
2309 void trim_scope_push(const string &name, const Interval &bound, vector<LetBound> &let_bounds) {
2310 // We want to add all the children of 'name' to 'let_bounds',
2311 // but avoiding duplicates (in some cases the dupes can
2312 // explode the list size by ~80x); note that the exact order
2313 // isn't important, as long as children are still visited
2314 // after parents. So we want to do a topological traversal of
2315 // the dependent lets.
2316
2317 // A recursive version of a topological traversal looks like:
2318 // 1) if node already visited, return
2319 // 2) mark node as visited
2320 // 3) recursively visit children
2321 // 4) prepend node to output list.
2322
2323 // Step 4 means that the node is the first thing in the output
2324 // list, and step 3 means all of the children have been
2325 // visited for sure and are in the output list somewhere
2326 // else. No future operations after this recursive step
2327 // returns ever move things around in the output list - we
2328 // only ever prepend things. This means we have the
2329 // topological sort property that every node is guaranteed to
2330 // be before all of its children.
2331
2332 // For an example of doing this the recursive way, see
2333 // realization_order_dfs in RealizationOrder.cpp. It uses two
2334 // different senses of 'visited' to check for cycles, but we
2335 // don't need that here. We'll assume there are no cycles.
2336
2337 // There could be many dependent lets, so we're going to do it
2338 // non-recursively with an explicit stack of Task structs
2339 // instead. Note that there's work to do (step 4) after the
2340 // recursive step (step 3), so we can't just discard nodes at
2341 // the same time as we enqueue their children. We need to
2342 // consider every node in the stack twice - once just before
2343 // pushing its children, and once again when we reach it again
2344 // after dealing with all children and it's time to pop it
2345 // (our pending stack is effectively a stack frame from the
2346 // recursive version).
2347
2348 // As a minor optimization we'll also do the visited
2349 // insert/check (steps 1 and 2) before pushing, so that
2350 // already-visited nodes don't even make it into the
2351 // stack. Finally, we actually want reverse topological order,
2352 // so we'll append nodes to the output instead of prepending.
2353
2354 struct Task {
2355 string var;
2356 bool visited_children_already;
2357 };
2358 vector<Task> pending;
2359 set<string> visited;
2360
2361 scope.push(name, bound);
2362 visited.insert(name);
2363 pending.push_back(Task{name, false});
2364
2365 // We don't want our root node 'name' in the let_bounds list,
2366 // so we'll stop when there's only one thing left in the
2367 // pending stack.
2368 do {
2369 Task &next = pending.back();
2370 if (!next.visited_children_already) {
2371 next.visited_children_already = true;
2372 // Note that pushing may invalidate the reference to next.
2373 for (const auto &v : children[get_var_instance(next.var)]) {
2374 if (visited.insert(v.var).second) {
2375 pending.push_back(Task{v.var, false});
2376 }
2377 }
2378 } else {
2379 string max_name = unique_name('t');
2380 string min_name = unique_name('t');
2381 let_bounds.emplace_back(next.var, min_name, max_name);
2382 Type t = let_stmts.get(next.var).type();
2383 Interval b = Interval(Variable::make(t, min_name), Variable::make(t, max_name));
2384 scope.push(next.var, b);
2385 pending.pop_back();
2386 }
2387 } while (pending.size() > 1);
2388 }
2389
2390 void trim_scope_pop(const string &name, vector<LetBound> &let_bounds) {
2391 for (const LetBound &l : let_bounds) {
2392 scope.pop(l.var);
2393 for (pair<const string, Box> &i : boxes) {
2394 Box &box = i.second;
2395 for (size_t i = 0; i < box.size(); i++) {
2396 Interval v_bound;
2397 if ((box[i].has_lower_bound() && (expr_uses_var(box[i].min, l.max_name) ||
2398 expr_uses_var(box[i].min, l.min_name))) ||
2399 (box[i].has_upper_bound() && (expr_uses_var(box[i].max, l.max_name) ||
2400 expr_uses_var(box[i].max, l.min_name)))) {
2401 internal_assert(let_stmts.contains(l.var));
2402 const Expr &val = let_stmts.get(l.var);
2403 v_bound = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(val, scope, func_bounds);
2404 bool fixed = v_bound.min.same_as(v_bound.max);
2405 v_bound.min = simplify(v_bound.min);
2406 v_bound.max = fixed ? v_bound.min : simplify(v_bound.max);
2407
2408 internal_assert(scope.contains(l.var));
2409 const Interval &old_bound = scope.get(l.var);
2410 v_bound.max = simplify(min(v_bound.max, old_bound.max));
2411 v_bound.min = simplify(max(v_bound.min, old_bound.min));
2412 }
2413
2414 if (box[i].has_lower_bound()) {
2415 if (expr_uses_var(box[i].min, l.max_name)) {
2416 box[i].min = Let::make(l.max_name, v_bound.max, box[i].min);
2417 }
2418 if (expr_uses_var(box[i].min, l.min_name)) {
2419 box[i].min = Let::make(l.min_name, v_bound.min, box[i].min);
2420 }
2421 }
2422 if (box[i].has_upper_bound()) {
2423 if (expr_uses_var(box[i].max, l.max_name)) {
2424 box[i].max = Let::make(l.max_name, v_bound.max, box[i].max);
2425 }
2426 if (expr_uses_var(box[i].max, l.min_name)) {
2427 box[i].max = Let::make(l.min_name, v_bound.min, box[i].max);
2428 }
2429 }
2430 }
2431 }
2432 }
2433 scope.pop(name);
2434 let_bounds.clear();
2435 }
2436
2437 vector<const Variable *> find_free_vars(const Expr &e) {
2438 class FindFreeVars : public IRVisitor {
2439 using IRVisitor::visit;
2440 void visit(const Variable *op) override {
2441 if (scope.contains(op->name)) {
2442 result.push_back(op);
2443 }
2444 }
2445
2446 public:
2447 const Scope<Interval> &scope;
2448 vector<const Variable *> result;
2449 FindFreeVars(const Scope<Interval> &s)
2450 : scope(s) {
2451 }
2452 } finder(scope);
2453 e.accept(&finder);
2454 return finder.result;
2455 }
2456
2457 void visit(const IfThenElse *op) override {
2458 op->condition.accept(this);
2459 if (expr_uses_vars(op->condition, scope)) {
2460 // We need to simplify the condition to get it into a
2461 // canonical form (e.g. (a < b) instead of !(a >= b))
2462 vector<pair<Expr, Stmt>> cases;
2463 {
2464 Expr c = simplify(op->condition);
2465 cases.emplace_back(c, op->then_case);
2466 if (op->else_case.defined() && !is_no_op(op->else_case)) {
2467 cases.emplace_back(simplify(!c), op->else_case);
2468 }
2469 }
2470 for (const auto &pair : cases) {
2471 Expr c = pair.first;
2472 Stmt body = pair.second;
2473 const Call *call = Call::as_tag(c);
2474 if (call) {
2475 c = call->args[0];
2476 }
2477
2478 // Find the vars that vary, and solve for each in turn
2479 // in order to bound it using the RHS. Maintain a list
2480 // of the things we need to pop from scope once we're
2481 // done.
2482 struct RestrictedVar {
2483 // This variable
2484 const Variable *v;
2485 // Takes on this range
2486 Interval i;
2487 // Implying that these other variables also have a restricted range
2488 vector<LetBound> let_bounds;
2489 };
2490 vector<RestrictedVar> to_pop;
2491 auto vars = find_free_vars(op->condition);
2492 for (const auto *v : vars) {
2493 auto result = solve_expression(c, v->name);
2494 if (!result.fully_solved) {
2495 continue;
2496 }
2497 Expr solved = result.result;
2498
2499 // Trim the scope down to represent the fact that the
2500 // condition is true. We only understand certain types
2501 // of conditions for now.
2502
2503 const LT *lt = solved.as<LT>();
2504 const LE *le = solved.as<LE>();
2505 const GT *gt = solved.as<GT>();
2506 const GE *ge = solved.as<GE>();
2507 const EQ *eq = solved.as<EQ>();
2508 Expr lhs, rhs;
2509 if (lt) {
2510 lhs = lt->a;
2511 rhs = lt->b;
2512 } else if (le) {
2513 lhs = le->a;
2514 rhs = le->b;
2515 } else if (gt) {
2516 lhs = gt->a;
2517 rhs = gt->b;
2518 } else if (ge) {
2519 lhs = ge->a;
2520 rhs = ge->b;
2521 } else if (eq) {
2522 lhs = eq->a;
2523 rhs = eq->b;
2524 }
2525
2526 if (!rhs.defined() || rhs.type() != Int(32)) {
2527 continue;
2528 }
2529
2530 if (!equal(lhs, v)) {
2531 continue;
2532 }
2533
2534 Expr inner_min, inner_max;
2535 Interval i = scope.get(v->name);
2536
2537 // If the original condition is likely, then
2538 // the additional trimming of the domain due
2539 // to the condition is probably unnecessary,
2540 // which means the mins/maxes below should
2541 // probably just be the LHS.
2542 Interval likely_i = i;
2543 if (call && call->is_intrinsic(Call::likely)) {
2544 likely_i.min = likely(i.min);
2545 likely_i.max = likely(i.max);
2546 } else if (call && call->is_intrinsic(Call::likely_if_innermost)) {
2547 likely_i.min = likely_if_innermost(i.min);
2548 likely_i.max = likely_if_innermost(i.max);
2549 }
2550
2551 Interval bi = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(rhs, scope, func_bounds);
2552 if (bi.has_upper_bound() && i.has_upper_bound()) {
2553 if (lt) {
2554 i.max = min(likely_i.max, bi.max - 1);
2555 }
2556 if (le || eq) {
2557 i.max = min(likely_i.max, bi.max);
2558 }
2559 }
2560 if (bi.has_lower_bound() && i.has_lower_bound()) {
2561 if (gt) {
2562 i.min = max(likely_i.min, bi.min + 1);
2563 }
2564 if (ge || eq) {
2565 i.min = max(likely_i.min, bi.min);
2566 }
2567 }
2568 RestrictedVar p;
2569 p.v = v;
2570 p.i = i;
2571 to_pop.emplace_back(std::move(p));
2572 }
2573 for (auto &p : to_pop) {
2574 trim_scope_push(p.v->name, p.i, p.let_bounds);
2575 }
2576 body.accept(this);
2577 while (!to_pop.empty()) {
2578 trim_scope_pop(to_pop.back().v->name, to_pop.back().let_bounds);
2579 to_pop.pop_back();
2580 }
2581 }
2582 } else {
2583 // If the condition is based purely on params, then we'll only
2584 // ever go one way in a given run, so we should conditionalize
2585 // the boxes touched on the condition.
2586
2587 // Fork the boxes touched and go down each path
2588 map<string, Box> then_boxes, else_boxes;
2589 then_boxes.swap(boxes);
2590 op->then_case.accept(this);
2591 then_boxes.swap(boxes);
2592
2593 if (op->else_case.defined()) {
2594 else_boxes.swap(boxes);
2595 op->else_case.accept(this);
2596 else_boxes.swap(boxes);
2597 }
2598
2599 // Make sure all the then boxes have an entry on the else
2600 // side so that the merge doesn't skip them.
2601 for (pair<const string, Box> &i : then_boxes) {
2602 else_boxes[i.first];
2603 }
2604
2605 // Merge
2606 for (pair<const string, Box> &i : else_boxes) {
2607 Box &else_box = i.second;
2608 Box &then_box = then_boxes[i.first];
2609 Box &orig_box = boxes[i.first];
2610
2611 if (then_box.maybe_unused()) {
2612 then_box.used = then_box.used && op->condition;
2613 } else {
2614 then_box.used = op->condition;
2615 }
2616
2617 if (else_box.maybe_unused()) {
2618 else_box.used = else_box.used && !op->condition;
2619 } else {
2620 else_box.used = !op->condition;
2621 }
2622
2623 merge_boxes(then_box, else_box);
2624 merge_boxes(orig_box, then_box);
2625 }
2626 }
2627 }
2628
2629 void visit(const For *op) override {
2630 if (consider_calls) {
2631 op->min.accept(this);
2632 op->extent.accept(this);
2633 }
2634
2635 Expr min_val, max_val;
2636 if (scope.contains(op->name + ".loop_min")) {
2637 min_val = scope.get(op->name + ".loop_min").min;
2638 } else {
2639 min_val = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(op->min, scope, func_bounds).min;
2640 }
2641
2642 if (scope.contains(op->name + ".loop_max")) {
2643 max_val = scope.get(op->name + ".loop_max").max;
2644 } else {
2645 max_val = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(op->extent, scope, func_bounds).max;
2646 max_val += bounds_of_expr_in_scope(op->min, scope, func_bounds).max;
2647 max_val -= 1;
2648 }
2649
2650 push_var(op->name);
2651 {
2652 ScopedBinding<Interval> p(scope, op->name, Interval(min_val, max_val));
2653 op->body.accept(this);
2654 }
2655 pop_var(op->name);
2656 }
2657
2658 void visit(const Provide *op) override {
2659 if (consider_provides) {
2660 if (op->name == func || func.empty()) {
2661 Box b(op->args.size());
2662 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
2663 b[i] = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(op->args[i], scope, func_bounds);
2664 }
2665 merge_boxes(boxes[op->name], b);
2666 }
2667 }
2668
2669 if (consider_calls) {
2670 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
2671 op->args[i].accept(this);
2672 }
2673 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->values.size(); i++) {
2674 op->values[i].accept(this);
2675 }
2676 }
2677 }
2678
2679 void visit(const ProducerConsumer *op) override {
2680 if (op->is_producer && (op->name == func || func.empty())) {
2681 ScopedValue<bool> save_in_producer(in_producer, true);
2682 IRGraphVisitor::visit(op);
2683 } else {
2684 IRGraphVisitor::visit(op);
2685 }
2686 }
2687};
2688
2689} // namespace
2690
2691map<string, Box> boxes_touched(const Expr &e, Stmt s, bool consider_calls, bool consider_provides,
2692 const string &fn, const Scope<Interval> &scope, const FuncValueBounds &fb) {
2693 if (!fn.empty() && s.defined()) {
2694 // Filter things down to the relevant sub-Stmts, so we don't spend a
2695 // long time reasoning about lets and ifs that don't surround an
2696 // access to the buffer in question.
2697
2698 class Filter : public IRMutator {
2699 using IRMutator::mutate;
2700 using IRMutator::visit;
2701
2702 bool relevant = false;
2703
2704 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
2705 if (op->name == fn) {
2706 relevant = true;
2707 return op;
2708 } else {
2709 return IRMutator::visit(op);
2710 }
2711 }
2712
2713 Stmt visit(const Provide *op) override {
2714 if (op->name == fn) {
2715 relevant = true;
2716 return op;
2717 } else {
2718 return IRMutator::visit(op);
2719 }
2720 }
2721
2722 Expr visit(const Variable *op) override {
2723 if (op->name == fn_buffer || op->name == fn) {
2724 relevant = true;
2725 }
2726 return op;
2727 }
2728
2729 public:
2730 Stmt mutate(const Stmt &s) override {
2731 bool old = relevant;
2732 relevant = false;
2733 Stmt s_new = IRMutator::mutate(s);
2734 if (!relevant) {
2735 relevant = old;
2736 return no_op;
2737 } else {
2738 return s_new;
2739 }
2740 }
2741
2742 const string &fn;
2743 const string fn_buffer;
2744 Stmt no_op;
2745 Filter(const string &fn)
2746 : fn(fn), fn_buffer(fn + ".buffer"), no_op(Evaluate::make(0)) {
2747 }
2748 } filter(fn);
2749
2750 s = filter.mutate(s);
2751 }
2752
2753 // Move the innermost vars in an IfThenElse's condition as far to the left
2754 // as possible, so that BoxesTouched can prune the variable scope tighter
2755 // when encountering the IfThenElse.
2756 if (s.defined()) {
2757 s = SolveIfThenElse().mutate(s);
2758 }
2759
2760 // Do calls and provides separately, for better simplification.
2761 BoxesTouched calls(consider_calls, false, fn, &scope, fb);
2762 BoxesTouched provides(false, consider_provides, fn, &scope, fb);
2763
2764 if (consider_calls) {
2765 if (e.defined()) {
2766 e.accept(&calls);
2767 }
2768 if (s.defined()) {
2769 s.accept(&calls);
2770 }
2771 }
2772 if (consider_provides) {
2773 if (e.defined()) {
2774 e.accept(&provides);
2775 }
2776 if (s.defined()) {
2777 s.accept(&provides);
2778 }
2779 }
2780 if (!consider_calls) {
2781 return provides.boxes;
2782 }
2783 if (!consider_provides) {
2784 return calls.boxes;
2785 }
2786
2787 // Combine the two maps.
2788 for (pair<const string, Box> &i : provides.boxes) {
2789 merge_boxes(calls.boxes[i.first], i.second);
2790 }
2791
2792 // Make evaluating these boxes side-effect-free
2793 for (auto &p : calls.boxes) {
2794 auto &box = p.second;
2795 box.used = purify_index_math(box.used);
2796 for (Interval &i : box.bounds) {
2797 i.min = purify_index_math(i.min);
2798 i.max = purify_index_math(i.max);
2799 }
2800 }
2801
2802 return calls.boxes;
2803}

2805Box box_touched(const Expr &e, Stmt s, bool consider_calls, bool consider_provides,
2806 const string &fn, const Scope<Interval> &scope, const FuncValueBounds &fb) {
2807 map<string, Box> boxes = boxes_touched(e, std::move(s), consider_calls, consider_provides, fn, scope, fb);
2808 internal_assert(boxes.size() <= 1);
2809 return boxes[fn];

2860// Compute interval of all possible function's values (default + specialized values)
2861Interval compute_pure_function_definition_value_bounds(
2862 const Definition &def, const Scope<Interval> &scope, const FuncValueBounds &fb, int dim) {
2863
2864 Interval result = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(def.values()[dim], scope, fb);
2865
2866 // Pure function might have different values due to specialization.
2867 // We need to take the union of min and max bounds of all those possible values.
2868 for (const Specialization &s : def.specializations()) {
2869 Interval s_interval = compute_pure_function_definition_value_bounds(s.definition, scope, fb, dim);
2870 result.include(s_interval);
2871 }
2872 return result;
2873}
2874
2875FuncValueBounds compute_function_value_bounds(const vector<string> &order,
2876 const map<string, Function> &env) {
2877 FuncValueBounds fb;
2878
2879 for (size_t i = 0; i < order.size(); i++) {
2880 Function f = env.find(order[i])->second;
2881 const vector<string> f_args = f.args();
2882 for (int j = 0; j < f.outputs(); j++) {
2883 pair<string, int> key = {f.name(), j};
2884
2885 Interval result;
2886
2887 if (f.is_pure()) {
2888
2889 // Make a scope that says the args could be anything.
2890 Scope<Interval> arg_scope;
2891 for (size_t k = 0; k < f.args().size(); k++) {
2892 arg_scope.push(f_args[k], Interval::everything());
2893 }
2894
2895 result = compute_pure_function_definition_value_bounds(f.definition(), arg_scope, fb, j);
2896 // These can expand combinatorially as we go down the
2897 // pipeline if we don't run CSE on them.
2898 if (result.has_lower_bound()) {
2899 result.min = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(result.min));
2900 }
2901
2902 if (result.has_upper_bound()) {
2903 result.max = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(result.max));
2904 }
2905
2906 fb[key] = result;
2907 } else {
2908 // If the Func is impure, we may still be able to specify a bounds-of-type here
2909 Type t = f.output_types()[j].element_of();
2910 if ((t.is_uint() || t.is_int()) && t.bits() <= 16) {
2911 result = Interval(t.min(), t.max());
2912 } else {
2913 result = Interval::everything();
2914 }
2915 fb[key] = result;
2916
2917 // TODO: if a Function is impure, but the RDoms used by the update functions
2918 // are all constant, it may be profitable to calculate the bounds here too
2919 }
2920
2921 debug(2) << "Bounds on value " << j
2922 << " for func " << order[i]
2923 << " are: " << result.min << ", " << result.max << "\n";
2924 }
2925 }
2926
2927 return fb;
2928}

2932void check(const Scope<Interval> &scope, const Expr &e, const Expr &correct_min, const Expr &correct_max) {
2933 FuncValueBounds fb;
2934 Interval result = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(e, scope, fb);
2935 result.min = simplify(result.min);
2936 result.max = simplify(result.max);
2937 if (!equal(result.min, correct_min)) {
2938 internal_error << "In bounds of " << e << ":\n"
2939 << "Incorrect min: " << result.min << "\n"
2940 << "Should have been: " << correct_min << "\n";
2941 }
2942 if (!equal(result.max, correct_max)) {
2943 internal_error << "In bounds of " << e << ":\n"
2944 << "Incorrect max: " << result.max << "\n"
2945 << "Should have been: " << correct_max << "\n";
2946 }
2947}

2949void check_constant_bound(const Scope<Interval> &scope, const Expr &e, const Expr &correct_min, const Expr &correct_max) {
2950 FuncValueBounds fb;
2951 Interval result = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(e, scope, fb, true);
2952 result.min = simplify(result.min);
2953 result.max = simplify(result.max);
2954 if (!equal(result.min, correct_min)) {
2955 internal_error << "In find constant bound of " << e << ":\n"
2956 << "Incorrect min constant bound: " << result.min << "\n"
2957 << "Should have been: " << correct_min << "\n";
2958 }
2959 if (!equal(result.max, correct_max)) {
2960 internal_error << "In find constant bound of " << e << ":\n"
2961 << "Incorrect max constant bound: " << result.max << "\n"
2962 << "Should have been: " << correct_max << "\n";
2963 }
2964}

2966void check_constant_bound(const Expr &e, const Expr &correct_min, const Expr &correct_max) {
2967 Scope<Interval> scope;
2968 check_constant_bound(scope, e, correct_min, correct_max);
2969}

3047 Interval::neg_inf(), Interval::pos_inf());

3049 {
3050 // Ensure that unnecessary integer overflow doesn't happen
3051 // in cases involving unsigned integer math
3052 Param<uint16_t> e1("e1"); // range 0..0xffff, type=uint16
3053 Expr e2 = cast<uint32_t>(e1); // range 0..0xffff, type=uint32
3054 Expr e3 = e2 * e2; // range 0..0xfffe0001, type=uint32
3055 check_constant_bound(e3, Expr((uint32_t)0), Expr((uint32_t)0xfffe0001));
3056 }
3057
3058 {
3059 RDom r(0, 4);
3060
3061 // bounds of an expression with impure >= 32 bit expr will be unbounded
3062 Expr e32 = sum(cast<int32_t>(r.x));
3063 check_constant_bound(e32, Interval::neg_inf(), Interval::pos_inf());
3064
3065 // bounds of an expression with impure < 32 bit expr will be bounds-of-type
3066 Expr e16 = sum(cast<int16_t>(r.x));
3067 check_constant_bound(e16, Int(16).min(), Int(16).max());
3068 }
3069
3070 {
3071 Param<int32_t> x("x"), y("y");
3072 x.set_range(2, 10);
3073
3074 check_constant_bound(count_leading_zeros(x), i32(28), i32(30));
3075 check_constant_bound(count_leading_zeros(cast<int16_t>(x)), i16(12), i16(14));
3076
3077 check_constant_bound(count_leading_zeros(y), i32(0), i32(32));
3078 check_constant_bound(count_leading_zeros(cast<int16_t>(y)), i16(0), i16(16));
3079 }
3080}

3082void boxes_touched_test() {
3083 Type t = Int(32);
3084 Expr x = Variable::make(t, "x");
3085 Expr y = Variable::make(t, "y");
3086 Expr z = Variable::make(t, "z");
3087 Expr w = Variable::make(t, "w");
3088
3089 Scope<Interval> scope;
3090 scope.push("y", Interval(Expr(0), Expr(10)));
3091
3092 Stmt stmt = Provide::make("f", {10}, {x, y, z, w});
3093 stmt = IfThenElse::make(y > 4, stmt, Stmt());
3094 stmt = IfThenElse::make(z > 18, stmt, Stmt());
3095 stmt = LetStmt::make("w", z + 3, stmt);
3096 stmt = LetStmt::make("z", x + 2, stmt);
3097 stmt = LetStmt::make("x", y + 10, stmt);
3098
3099 Box expected({Interval(15, 20), Interval(5, 10), Interval(19, 22), Interval(22, 25)});
3100 Box result = box_provided(stmt, "f", scope);
3101 internal_assert(expected.size() == result.size())
3102 << "Expect dim size of " << expected.size()
3103 << ", got " << result.size() << " instead\n";
3104 for (size_t i = 0; i < result.size(); ++i) {
3105 const Interval &correct = expected[i];
3106 Interval b = result[i];
3107 b.min = simplify(b.min);
3108 b.max = simplify(b.max);
3109 if (!equal(correct.min, b.min)) {
3110 internal_error << "In bounds of dim " << i << ":\n"
3111 << "Incorrect min: " << b.min << "\n"
3112 << "Should have been: " << correct.min << "\n";
3113 }
3114 if (!equal(correct.max, b.max)) {
3115 internal_error << "In bounds of dim " << i << ":\n"
3116 << "Incorrect max: " << b.max << "\n"
3117 << "Should have been: " << correct.max << "\n";
3118 }
3119 }
3120}
